binder
Homonym Number:  1
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a solid meal, or a meal after some fast e.g. a cooked breakfast).
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: [P: a (good, satisfying) meal: NZers': 20C. OED2 9. A large quantity, esp. of food; a satisfying meal. Dial and NZ coll.: 1881 Isle of Wight Words; cf EDD n2 Large quantity, esp. of food. IW, Hmp; nf W3]
